math.shell.linearAlgebra.calculator

Class Matrix

  • java.lang.Object
    • math.shell.linearAlgebra.calculator.Matrix

  • public class Matrix
extends Object
    Constructs a Matrix object that can be used for linear algebra purposes. Values in the Matrix are of type BigDecimal. The Matrix holds identifing information such as if it is a 2x2, 3x3, square, identity, diagonal, triangular, upper triangular, lower triangular, or symmetrix Matrix.
    Version:
    1.1
    Author:
    Avraham Katz

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Converts a Matrix to its string representation String represenation starts with '[' and ends with ']׳. A comma denotes a new value, moving from value in (i,j) to (i,j+1). A '|' denotes moving to the next line, moving from (i,j) to (i+1,j). Example: |1 2| |3 4| = "[1,2|3,4|]" |1 0 0| |0 1 0| = "[1,0,0|0,1,0|]"
        Overrides:
        toString in class Object
        Returns:
        String String represenation of Matrix
